# Puppeteer MCP Server Settings
# Use this file to configure the Puppeteer MCP server for Claude Desktop
#
# Format:
# SETTING_NAME=value
#
# Optional Settings:
# -----------------
# CONTAINER_NAME - Name of the Docker container (default: puppeteer-mcp-server)
# DOCKER_IMAGE - Docker image name and tag (default: mcp/puppeteer:latest)
# RESTART_CLAUDE - Whether to restart Claude Desktop if it's running (true/false, default: true)
# BROWSER_HEADLESS - Whether to run browser in headless mode (true/false, default: true)
# BROWSER_WIDTH - Default browser viewport width (default: 1280)
# BROWSER_HEIGHT - Default browser viewport height (default: 800)
# SCREENSHOT_DIR - Directory to save screenshots (default: ./screenshots)
#
# Examples:
# CONTAINER_NAME=my-puppeteer-server
# DOCKER_IMAGE=mcp/puppeteer:custom
# RESTART_CLAUDE=false
# BROWSER_HEADLESS=false
# BROWSER_WIDTH=1920
# BROWSER_HEIGHT=1080
# SCREENSHOT_DIR=/path/to/screenshots
#
# Default settings (uncomment and modify as needed):
# CONTAINER_NAME=puppeteer-mcp-server
# DOCKER_IMAGE=mcp/puppeteer:latest
# RESTART_CLAUDE=true
# BROWSER_HEADLESS=true
# BROWSER_WIDTH=1280
# BROWSER_HEIGHT=800
# SCREENSHOT_DIR=./screenshots
